>>f7b2f01d-6eb2-42cf-a973-79f04f4c5127
Anyone who has half the brain cells required to get here should be able to see, with the recent events of 8chan and Sadpanda, just how impermanent and susceptible to censorship traditional clearnet sites are. I understand the need to go back (I will myself) but I also strongly encourage anyone who's made it this far not to take a technological step backwards by leaving this place empty. Distributed P2P networking is the next step for fringe/objectionable/"lawless" communities such as imageboards. I personally believe that the barrier to entry (extracting zip files is a foreign concept to most redditors/normalfags and probably cuckchanners with the current state of 4cuck) and user based moderation though [M] will increase post quality. **Also why go back to being a regular old internet racist when you could be a sp00ky darkweb cyberpunk supern4z1s?** I sincerely hope that anons will help this place flourish, at least along side 8chan, if not instead of it.
